  "text": "Threshold for domain size and obstacles. Intuitively, one can expect that if L is small, y = a will be the only solution to the previous stationary problem, while if L is large, there might be others. It is indeed well-known that there exists a threshold for L under which a is the only solution, and above which there is at least one other [CITATION_1] .",
